Seville first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Seville had a population of 446. The population density was {{convert|1,621.8|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Seville was 81 (18.2%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 27 (6.1%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 1 (0.2%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 208 (46.6%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 129 (28.9%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 419 persons (93.9%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Seville CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0671078 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 99 households, out of which 50 (50.5%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 51 (51.5%) were married-couple households, 8 (8.1%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 20 (20.2%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 20 (20.2%) had a male householder with no partner present. 17 households (17.2%) were one person, and 4 (4.0%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 4.51.<ref name=DP1/> There were 77 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (77.8% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Seville CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0671078 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 147 people (33.0%) under the age of 18, 54 people (12.1%) aged 18 to 24, 126 people (28.3%) aged 25 to 44, 81 people (18.2%) aged 45 to 64, and 38 people (8.5%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 27.1{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 98.2 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 105 housing units at an average density of {{convert|381.8|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 99 (94.3%) were occupied. Of these, 47 (47.5%) were owner-occupied, and 52 (52.5%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

